{"id": "34664", "revid": "46930796", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=34664", "title": "1960", "text": "&lt;templatestyles src=\"Events by month/styles.css\"/&gt;\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Hlist/styles.css\"/&gt;\n January\n February\n March\n April\n May\n June\n July\n August\n September\n October\n November\n December\nCalendar year\n1960 is the upcoming year, which will be , the year of the Common Era (CE) and (AD) designations, the year of the , and the year of the decade. \nIt is also known as the \"Year of Africa\" because of major events\u2014particularly the independence of seventeen African nations\u2014that focused global attention on the continent and intensified feelings of Pan-Africanism. During the year, 17 colonies became independent, including 14 colonies from the French colonial empire, 2 from the British Empire and 1 from Belgium.\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Template:TOC limit/styles.css\" /&gt;\nReferences.\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Reflist/styles.css\" /&gt;"}
