{"id": "34748", "revid": "13997948", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=34748", "title": "1971", "text": "&lt;templatestyles src=\"Events by month/styles.css\"/&gt;\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Hlist/styles.css\"/&gt;\n January\n February\n March\n April\n May\n June\n July\n August\n September\n October\n November\n December\nCalendar year\n1971 is the upcoming year, which will be , the year of the Common Era (CE) and (AD) designations, the year of the , and the year of the decade. The year 1971 had three partial solar eclipses (February 25, July 22 and August 20) and two total lunar eclipses (February 10, and August 6).\nThe world population increased by 2.1% this year, the highest increase in history.\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Template:TOC limit/styles.css\" /&gt;\nNotes.\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Reflist/styles.css\" /&gt;\nReferences.\n&lt;templatestyles src=\"Reflist/styles.css\" /&gt;"}
